785
00:46:39,129 --> 00:46:42,966
So every kind of trouble has come my way
even the trouble of aging

786
00:46:43,592 --> 00:46:44,885
I need to lose weight, right?

787
00:46:44,968 --> 00:46:47,012
Yikes, this fate is really cold

788
00:46:47,513 --> 00:46:50,015
An orphan all alone in this world

789
00:46:52,434 --> 00:46:53,769
How can that not change?

790
00:46:54,144 --> 00:46:57,898
A life like a small sailing boat adrift
in the vast ocean.

791
00:46:57,981 --> 00:47:01,902
I wish there was a handsome man on that boat

792
00:47:01,985 --> 00:47:04,071
Oh, I see him, the man

793
00:47:04,154 --> 00:47:07,533
Be careful of the man with the hat, the pitch-black hat

794
00:47:07,783 --> 00:47:10,911
I hope that man with the hat is handsome

795
00:47:17,334 --> 00:47:18,377
(Kim Shin)
Where are you going?

796
00:47:20,128 --> 00:47:21,088
(The Grim Reaper)
The laundromat

797
00:47:22,089 --> 00:47:23,799
It's dry cleaning only, this is

798
00:47:24,341 --> 00:47:27,010
I feel this every time
That hat is really a great concept

799
00:47:27,094 --> 00:47:29,263
Making the dead look silly on their last journey

800
00:47:31,265 --> 00:47:32,182
[SIGH]

801
00:47:32,849 --> 00:47:36,019
'Do not seek death
for death will seek you'

802
00:47:36,853 --> 00:47:38,355
It's based on that item

803
00:47:38,438 --> 00:47:40,065
You have to write this for the deceased to recognize.

804
00:47:40,148 --> 00:47:41,441
It's not visible to the eyes of humans.

805
00:47:41,525 --> 00:47:45,195
(Kim Shin)
Oh, it's a relief that it's not visible to human eyes.
It would be so embarrassing.

806
00:47:45,404 --> 00:47:46,446
Have a good trip.

807
00:47:52,202 --> 00:47:53,996
[LIVELY MUSIC]

808
00:48:19,271 --> 00:48:20,188
[A BREATH MIXED WITH IRRITATION]

809
00:48:27,195 --> 00:48:28,864
Don’t you have to iron it?

810
00:48:29,615 --> 00:48:31,241
When are you from?

811
00:48:31,325 --> 00:48:33,201
These days, it sticks well just like this.

812
00:48:33,535 --> 00:48:36,455
And you,
who coats the leaves these days?

813
00:48:37,122 --> 00:48:39,875
It's fine since the person receiving this is a bit older.

814
00:48:40,000 --> 00:48:42,377
(Jung Hyun)
Who? Did you get a boyfriend?

815
00:48:42,461 --> 00:48:43,503
Hey!

816
00:48:43,879 --> 00:48:45,380
What about my boyfriend?

817
00:48:46,882 --> 00:48:50,218
I'm just grateful because he helped me find a part-time job.

818
00:48:50,802 --> 00:48:53,889
But what if he misunderstands this?
Saying I like him

819
00:48:54,473 --> 00:48:58,477
He’s someone who denies my very existence
I guess he wouldn’t think that way

820
00:49:07,653 --> 00:49:08,570
[HE BLOWS HOT AIR]

821
00:49:15,369 --> 00:49:17,746
Mister, I brought you a gift...

822
00:49:17,871 --> 00:49:19,831
[TENSE MUSIC]

823
00:49:24,753 --> 00:49:27,673
(Euntak)
Ah, I left my scarf, my scarf

824
00:49:27,756 --> 00:49:28,632
(Reaper)
As expected

825
00:49:29,591 --> 00:49:32,803
You can see me
Even 10 years ago, and now

826
00:49:33,178 --> 00:49:34,346
The lines are the same

827
00:49:34,429 --> 00:49:36,765
What if the boss locked the door?

828
00:49:36,848 --> 00:49:37,933
(Euntak)
Ah, fool

829
00:49:38,016 --> 00:49:39,142
[MYSTERIOUS SOUND EFFECT]

830
00:49:39,726 --> 00:49:42,229
(Grim Reaper)
It's useless, I know everything that's visible

831
00:49:42,312 --> 00:49:44,064
Now there's no one left to protect you

832
00:49:44,940 --> 00:49:45,982
[SIGH]

833
00:49:48,068 --> 00:49:49,778
I know I've been caught too

834
00:49:51,446 --> 00:49:52,531
(Grim Reaper)
You moved, right?

835
00:49:53,323 --> 00:49:56,535
Thanks to that, I've been looking for you for 10 years
and today I finally see you

836
00:49:56,618 --> 00:49:58,161
Then why not just stop looking?

837
00:49:58,245 --> 00:50:01,456
(Euntak)
At this point, in the living world
they would call me a stalker, you know?

838
00:50:02,666 --> 00:50:03,792
I'm going to sue!

839
00:50:04,167 --> 00:50:05,502
My name isn't even on the list

840
00:50:05,585 --> 00:50:07,379
But I'm on the list of other omissions.

841
00:50:07,713 --> 00:50:10,757
(Grim Reaper)
It must be a headache due to the 19 years' worth of evidence documents

842
00:50:13,969 --> 00:50:14,928
Then

843
00:50:16,471 --> 00:50:17,931
What happens to me now?

844
00:50:20,267 --> 00:50:21,309
Am I going to die?

845
00:50:22,644 --> 00:50:24,438
(Euntak)
I'm only nineteen now?

846
00:50:25,605 --> 00:50:29,234
You can die at nine and ten

847
00:50:29,317 --> 00:50:30,861
[HEAVY MUSIC]

848
00:50:30,944 --> 00:50:32,070
That's death

849
00:50:33,655 --> 00:50:34,656
(Grim Reaper)
But

850
00:50:35,532 --> 00:50:38,118
This time, who are you with, anyway?

851
00:50:41,496 --> 00:50:42,372
[EUNTAK'S SURPRISED BREATH]

852
00:50:42,956 --> 00:50:44,750
(Euntak)
Close your eyes, we can't make eye contact.

853
00:50:44,833 --> 00:50:46,376
[In a small voice]
That person is a grim reaper.

854
00:51:00,724 --> 00:51:03,059
(Euntak)
No, we can't make eye contact.

855
00:51:09,691 --> 00:51:10,942
It's okay, we know each other.

856
00:51:16,031 --> 00:51:17,282
(Kim Shin)
Are you working?

857
00:51:18,408 --> 00:51:21,536
(Grim Reaper)
I am, but I don't know what you're doing.

858
00:51:21,620 --> 00:51:23,413
I'm involved in the life and death of humans.

859
00:51:23,497 --> 00:51:26,041
(Grim Reaper)
So it seems like you're making a big mistake.

860
00:51:26,666 --> 00:51:29,127
This child has already been...

861
00:51:29,211 --> 00:51:31,755
[THUNDER RUMBLES]

862
00:51:40,347 --> 00:51:42,307
Do I look like I want to hear an explanation?

863
00:51:43,600 --> 00:51:44,434
[TENSE MUSIC]

864
00:51:44,518 --> 00:51:47,187
(Kim Shin)
When the goblin is serious,
didn't you learn not to listen carelessly?

865
00:51:47,646 --> 00:51:50,816
Be careful, because I might want to get involved
even in your life and death

866
00:51:53,735 --> 00:51:54,903
For now, run away

867
00:51:54,986 --> 00:51:57,155
If you run, there's a way, this way

868
00:52:01,201 --> 00:52:03,453
It's okay, just stay
because I can't take you away

869
00:52:03,537 --> 00:52:05,330
Just a while ago, you said you
were looking for me for 10 years...

870
00:52:05,413 --> 00:52:06,248
Still

871
00:52:07,249 --> 00:52:09,334
Even if I had been looking for you for 100 years, still

872
00:52:10,544 --> 00:52:13,713
No lion can take away
a girl who wants to marry a goblin

873
00:52:13,964 --> 00:52:15,924
[MEANINGFUL MUSIC]

874
00:52:16,007 --> 00:52:17,551
Right in front of the goblin

875
00:52:18,385 --> 00:52:21,429
(Grim Reaper)
Oh, then could it be that guy...

876
00:52:21,888 --> 00:52:23,640
Yes, that's right, that's me

877
00:52:23,723 --> 00:52:25,559
The goblin bride with a lot of rumors

878
00:52:26,726 --> 00:52:27,894
(Eun-tak)
So what are you going to do now?

879
00:52:28,562 --> 00:52:29,813
Are you still going to take me away?

880
00:52:29,896 --> 00:52:31,898
[THE SIREN WAILS]

881
00:52:35,485 --> 00:52:38,071
Given the atmosphere
it seems I'm the bad guy

882
00:52:38,864 --> 00:52:40,407
I'm in a hurry too, so

883
00:52:40,490 --> 00:52:42,200
let's talk in detail later

884
00:52:42,909 --> 00:52:44,035
We'll meet again

885
00:52:44,119 --> 00:52:47,664
(Grim Reaper)
Coincidences like today are nice
or feel free to make a plan with me

886
00:52:53,628 --> 00:52:54,713
[A SIGH OF RELIEF]

887
00:52:58,174 --> 00:52:59,134
Speak

888
00:52:59,843 --> 00:53:01,636
You have so much to say on your face

889
00:53:08,018 --> 00:53:08,977
See

890
00:53:10,228 --> 00:53:11,521
You're a goblin, right?

891
00:53:12,689 --> 00:53:13,815
I knew it

892
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:17,652
But why did you lie and say you’re not a goblin?

893
00:53:17,736 --> 00:53:19,821
At first, I didn't think I would see you again

894
00:53:19,946 --> 00:53:20,864
[CALM MUSIC]

895
00:53:20,947 --> 00:53:22,324
(Kim Shin)
Did you think you would come in?

896
00:53:22,824 --> 00:53:25,201
Into my door, where no one has ever
followed me in before

897
00:53:25,285 --> 00:53:26,328
And then what?

898
00:53:27,329 --> 00:53:29,080
I asked several times after that

899
00:53:29,164 --> 00:53:31,166
Then there was no need to correct it.

900
00:53:31,833 --> 00:53:34,252
(Kim Shin)
From the beginning until now
Maybe in the future you

901
00:53:35,045 --> 00:53:36,713
are not a goblin bride

902
00:53:42,510 --> 00:53:43,511
Then what am I

903
00:53:45,347 --> 00:53:46,306
? What is this?

904
00:53:50,852 --> 00:53:52,854
The ghosts every day
keep talking about that 'goblin'

905
00:53:52,938 --> 00:53:54,272
and come to talk to me

906
00:53:55,106 --> 00:53:58,985
If I don't see them, they bother me
and if I do see them, they cling to me

907
00:54:00,528 --> 00:54:02,030
I'm living like this

908
00:54:03,031 --> 00:54:05,116
but the afterlife agents
say I shouldn't be alive

909
00:54:06,618 --> 00:54:08,161
So what am I

910
00:54:09,245 --> 00:54:12,207
? I told you, it's something you have to bear

911
00:54:12,290 --> 00:54:13,917
It doesn't seem like something you should argue with me about

912
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:15,669
Ha, that's petty.

913
00:54:15,877 --> 00:54:18,588
[Sniffling]
It's so pathetic

914
00:54:20,423 --> 00:54:21,383
[I AM SOBBING]

915
00:54:22,300 --> 00:54:25,136
What? If I met a goblin
Would I really be trying to get married?

916
00:54:25,929 --> 00:54:28,098
(Euntak)
Honestly, tell me, is there another reason?

917
00:54:29,599 --> 00:54:34,020
Is it because I'm not pretty
That you said I'm not a goblin?

918
00:54:35,230 --> 00:54:37,691
That I'm too far from your ideal type?

919
00:54:38,441 --> 00:54:40,151
[Kim Shin's absurd breath]
That's right!

920
00:54:40,235 --> 00:54:41,861
- No
- (Euntak) What? You always say no!

921
00:54:41,945 --> 00:54:43,738
(Euntak)
You said I wasn't a goblin, but you were right

922
00:54:43,822 --> 00:54:44,864
You're pretty

923
00:54:44,948 --> 00:54:45,907
[SURPRISED BREATH]

924
00:54:48,535 --> 00:54:50,286
I've lived for over 900 years.

925
00:54:51,287 --> 00:54:53,248
I'm not looking for a pretty person.

926
00:54:53,331 --> 00:54:56,042
I'm looking for someone who can discover something
in me.

927
00:54:56,918 --> 00:54:58,920
(Kim Shin)
That's why
you, who can't discover anything,

928
00:54:59,004 --> 00:55:00,463
are not the goblin bride

929
00:55:00,547 --> 00:55:01,715
That's just how it is.

930
00:55:02,757 --> 00:55:04,968
The fact that you have no utility value
is also what it means.

931
00:55:05,260 --> 00:55:06,177
[SIGH]

932
00:55:06,970 --> 00:55:08,555
It's so sharp that it hurts.

933
00:55:08,638 --> 00:55:09,764
There's nothing to be hurt by.

934
00:55:11,016 --> 00:55:12,350
Rather, consider it a blessing.

935
00:55:14,477 --> 00:55:16,646
(Kim Shin)
If you had discovered something in me,

936
00:55:18,565 --> 00:55:20,316
You must have really blamed me a lot

937
00:55:23,737 --> 00:55:25,739
Then why do you say you're not a goblin until the end?

938
00:55:26,448 --> 00:55:27,782
Why are you bringing it up now?

939
00:55:27,866 --> 00:55:29,868
For the same reason you said it wasn't true

940
00:55:30,994 --> 00:55:33,204
(Kim Shin)
Don't call me out with pointless false hopes

941
00:55:34,706 --> 00:55:36,249
I'm about to leave here soon

942
00:55:39,544 --> 00:55:40,670
Where to?

943
00:55:45,216 --> 00:55:47,302
No, don't answer that

944
00:55:47,719 --> 00:55:48,636
[I’M SNIFFLING]

945
00:55:48,720 --> 00:55:50,055
Not curious at all

946
00:55:51,139 --> 00:55:52,766
Who says you're an uncle priest?

947
00:55:53,308 --> 00:55:55,310
Did I go mad at the beautiful age of nineteen?

948
00:55:56,102 --> 00:55:58,980
I won't call you out again
So live with a peaceful mind.

949
00:55:59,397 --> 00:56:01,024
I don't need an uncle either.

950
00:56:02,442 --> 00:56:06,863
Just thinking, 'Oh, so that's what a goblin looks like'

951
00:56:33,598 --> 00:56:34,599
[SNIFF]

952
00:56:49,155 --> 00:56:50,365
(grim reaper)
Are you finally dying?

953
00:56:51,533 --> 00:56:54,327
Rumor has it that when a bride appears
you die.

954
00:56:54,661 --> 00:56:57,497
Unfortunately, you can't die
he can't see the sword.

955
00:56:57,580 --> 00:56:59,290
Well, he might still not be able to see it.

956
00:56:59,374 --> 00:57:02,085
Sigh, or maybe you have to be completely naked to see it.

957
00:57:02,168 --> 00:57:03,253
(grim reaper)
The kid is still young.

958
00:57:03,336 --> 00:57:05,171
Since the kid is still young, don't even think about it.

959
00:57:06,172 --> 00:57:08,258
(grim reaper)
Why are you protecting him? You said he can't even see the sword.

960
00:57:08,341 --> 00:57:11,094
Just congratulations
Because you've lived longer

961
00:57:11,177 --> 00:57:12,220
Go live long somewhere else

962
00:57:12,303 --> 00:57:15,306
(Grim Reaper)
I can't live with a goblin that interferes with my life and death

963
00:57:15,390 --> 00:57:17,308
There's a very easy way for you to leave

964
00:57:17,934 --> 00:57:19,018
The exit is over there

965
00:57:21,020 --> 00:57:21,980
[SIGH]

966
00:57:22,564 --> 00:57:23,523
